[ANALYSIS]
The experiment `bow_opt_20260514_180714_run_03` using a Bag of Words (BoW) architecture with TF-IDF vectorization achieved a reasonable performance, as indicated by an F1 score of 0.7143 and accuracy of 0.75. The optimal threshold for classification was found to be 0.41. However, the experiment did not explore different values for `logreg_c`, which controls the regularization strength in logistic regression; this could potentially lead to better performance. Additionally, varying the `min_df` parameter might help in reducing noise by excluding less frequent words that may not contribute significantly to the model's predictive power. For the next run, it would be beneficial to conduct a grid search or random search over a range of values for `logreg_c` and `min_df`, as well as other hyperparameters like `ngram_max` and `max_features`, to systematically identify the best configuration for this dataset.